    en: 'Italy relies on sector-based national collective agreements (Contratti Collettivi Nazionali di Lavoro, or CCNL) to set minimum pay. These agreements are negotiated between employer associations and trade unions for each industry sector. Over 900 CCNLs exist, covering approximately 97% of workers. While there have been debates about introducing a statutory minimum, Italy has maintained its collective bargaining model, which the EU Minimum Wage Directive (2022/2041) also recognizes as a valid approach.',
    fr: 'L\'Italie s\'appuie sur des conventions collectives nationales sectorielles (CCNL) pour fixer les salaires minimums. Ces accords sont négociés entre les organisations patronales et les syndicats pour chaque secteur. Plus de 900 CCNL existent, couvrant environ 97% des travailleurs.',
